sentences: Ian Koromah (born 1995), better known by the stage name Maxsta, is an English grime MC from South East London.
Koromah was born in Lewisham, London, in 1995.
As a child he was initially into rock music and skateboarding before becoming interested in grime, being introduced to it through JME's "Shut Your Mouth" and Ghetto's "2000 and Life".
On 30 June 2009, Koromah released East London Is Back, a "stunningly spartan Atari teenage riot of electro bloops and beeps".
This paved the way for a mixtape, The Maxtape, released on 29 March 2010.
It was a commercial success, selling out in the first few days.
Shortly afterwards, Koromah performed at T in the Park 2010.
His new musical direction was reflected in the song Average Kid, which was released in early 2011.
Shortly afterwards, in March 2011, Koromah was signed to Just Jam Records, a subsidiary of Sony Music Entertainment.
Subsequently, Koromah featured in the 2011 Google Chrome advert, the second most popular YouTube advert of the year.
